parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column locking system can cause the steering wheel to seize or lock, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stuck or locked
the "Service Column Lock" warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
and the driver is unable to unlock the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the recall repair to properly address the steering column locking issue can lead to recurring problems, leaving the driver at risk of accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The steering wheel continues to lock or seize after the recall repair
the "Service Column Lock" warning light continues to illuminate
and the vehicle stalls or shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to notify vehicle owners of the recall can lead to delayed or missed repairs, leaving the driver at risk of accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The vehicle owner is not notified of the recall
despite the vehicle being eligible for repair
and the owner is not aware of the potential safety risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the aluminum wheels can cause the tire to lose air pressure, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or strandings, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracks in the spokes or rim of the wheel
loss of air pressure
tire failure
vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EBCM can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS), Traction Control System, and Stability Control System to malfunction, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: ABS and Traction Control lights illuminate on the dashboard
Service Active Handling notification appears
brake pedal jerks back and forth
brakes lock up without pressing the pedal
vehicle pulls to one side
loss of brake function
and warning lights stay on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Excessive Rusting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Brakes fail while backing out of the garage
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: ABS service light illuminates on the dashboard
ABS system failure
brakes lock up without pressing the pedal
vehicle pulls to one side
loss of brake function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control and airbag systems can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Cruise control accelerates unexpectedly
airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
ABS brakes lock up when pressed hard.
